In the last complete year of data (2015), WHO (http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/250142/1/WER9138.pdf?ua=1) reported a total of 172 454 cases worldwide in 42 countries. This continuing cholera disaster in Yemen is only about 10 weeks old and is rapidly approaching twice the whole 2015 total of cases. - Mod.LL

